{"whyJoin":"I’m currently a student at UT Austin but I’ve loved meeting new people at farmers markets and other Austin events (mueller domain aboretum) and the ppl of Austin r just so sweet and amazing so id love to branch out and make new friends outside of my current social circles. ","guestType":"investigator","socialBravery":"I volunteer at Micah 6 to offer free blood pressure and blood sugar screenings to the people there. Oftentimes they decline, or aren’t able to respond because they’re busy bees which can be a little taxing on confidence - but it is so rewarding if im able to help even just one person per shift, so I keep on volunteering and I keep on asking :))!","passion":"Baking! I used to work at a dessert shop hauling cakes in the back but also latte art - I love love trying new sourdough bread inclusions rn - I recently did a blueberry chocolate loaf and it turned out super pretty. I’ve also hosted a cafe pop up with my friends and that was super fun!! 

I rlly rlly enjoyed Bridgerton and watching the one piece live action too!  

Additionally I currently work in healthcare and am super curious about public health and the different specialties / work that makes up the whole medical team. "}
